<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-08-11T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-08-11T12:00:00-05:00" n="488" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d488">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.105/388: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">McGurk</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-08-11T12:00:00-05:00">August 11,
                                1931—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:50 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>99. Legation’s 77, July 10, noon. The President signed Aarons’ commission
                            and delivered it to the Commandant of the Garde today.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">McGurk</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>